children.name: Rules
children.text: A saddle with a higher cantle and horn, which provides more stability during daring stunts and maneuvers. Many such saddles are decorated with horns, bones, or feathers. While riding a mount outfitted with the saddle, any time a difficult maneuver causes you to make a Wisdom (Animal Handling) check, you can choose to make a Dexterity (Acrobatics) check instead. In addition, while mounted, you can use a bonus action to gain a +2 bonus to AC and Dexterity saving throws until the start of your next turn.
